                    <p style="font-family: 'Varela Round', sans-serif;">To understand our purpose in the world, we need to first understand the goal of every life and how it all works. </p>
					<p style="font-family: 'Varela Round', sans-serif;">Per the Vedanta ideology and many other philosophies, the supreme goal of every life is to know the self, by which, it means to know and be one with the ultimate reality also known as Brahman (Hinduism/Vedanta), Yahweh (Judaism), God (Christianity), Allah (Islam).</p>
					<p style="font-family: 'Varela Round', sans-serif;">To achieve this, one goes through the churn of many births. In each birth, he is assigned a purpose or karma. It is through this Karma that he learns his lessons, gains knowledge and achieves success.</p>
					<p style="font-family: 'Varela Round', sans-serif;">Karma or Purpose of life in a simple way is like saying <span style="color:#d60a61;">“What we are here to do.”</span> There is no denying or resenting this. Having said that, to fulfil our Karma/Purpose and achieve success, we are also given many inherent material strengths and gifts. These are available to use to make a life peaceful and happy.</p>
					<p style="font-family: 'Varela Round', sans-serif;">Thankfully, through the science of Numerology (analysed through the principles of NaamVidya) we can understand this purpose well, including the strengths given.
					This, derived from the details of a Date of Birth can be used to understand a person's true inner nature and his talents.</p>
					<p style="font-family: 'Varela Round', sans-serif;">A name aligned to this plane of Life’s Purpose and Strengths draws a path of success that is pleasant and rewarding.</p>
